obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24124)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24124&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Metro Railways`
  line `(Construction of Works) Act, 1978.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) It applies in the first instance to the metropolitan city of Calcutta; and the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that this Act shall also apply to ^2[the National Capital`
  line `Region, such other metropolitan city and metropolitan area, after consultation with the State Government,`
  line `and with effect from such date as may be specified in that notification and thereupon the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply to the National Capital Region, such metropolitan city or metropolitan area`
  line accordingly.]
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st February, 1979, vide notification No. S.O. 412(E), dated 20th January, 1979, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24125)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24125&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Advisory Board" means the Advisory Board constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) ^1["appellate authority"] means the appellate authority appointed under section 16;`
  line
  line `(c) "building" means a house, outhouse, stable, latrine, urinal, shed, hut or wall or any other`
  line `structure or erection, whether of masonry bricks, wood, mud, metal or any other material or any part`
  line `of a building, but does not include a plant or machinery installed in a building or any part thereof or`
  line `any portable shelter;`
  line
  line `(d) "commissioner" means a commissioner of metro railway appointed under section 27;`
  line
  line `^2["(e) competent authority" means the competent authority appointed under section 16;]`
  line
  line `(f) "development" with its grammatical variations means the carrying out of building,`
  line `engineering, mining or other operations in, on, over or under land or the making of any material`
  line `change in any building or land or planting of any tree on land and includes redevelopment;`
  line
  line `(g) "land" includes any right or interest in land;`
  line
  line `(h) "metro alignment", in relation to any ^3[metropolitan city, metropolitan area and the National`
  line `Capital Region] means such alignment of the metro railway as is specified in the Schedule under that`
  line `city and includes the metro railway;`
  line
  line `^4[(ha) "metropolitan area" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (c) of article 243P of`
  line `the Constitution;]`
  line
  line `(i) "metro railway" means a metro railway or any portion thereof for the public carriage of`
  line `passengers, animals or goods and includes,--`
  line
  line `(a) all land within the boundary marks indicating the limits of the land appurtenant to a metro`
  line railway,
  line
  line `(b) all lines of rails, sidings, yards or branches worked over for the purposes of, or in`
  line `connection with, a metro railway,`
  line
  line `(c) all stations, offices, ventilation shafts and ducts, warehouses, workshops, manufactories,`
  line `fixed plants and machineries, sheds, depots and other works constructed for the purpose of, or in`
  line `connection with, a metro railway;`
  line
  line `(j) "metro railway administration", in relation to any metro railway, means the General Manager`
  line `of that metro railway;`
  line
  line `(k) "metropolitan city" means the metropolitan city of Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi or Madras;`
  line
  line `(l) "metropolitan city of Bombay" means the area covered by Greater Bombay as defined in the`
  line `Bombay Municipal Corporation Act, 1888 (Bombay Act III 1888);`
  line
  line `(m) "metropolitan city of Calcutta" means the area described under the heading l. Calcutta`
  line `Metropolitan District in the Schedule to the Calcutta Metropolitan Planning Area (Use and`
  line `Development of Land) Control Act, 1965 (West Bengal Act XIV of 1965);`
  line
  line `(n) "metropolitan city of Delhi" means the entire area of the Union territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(o) "metropolitan city of Madras" means the area covered by the City of Madras as defined in the`
  line `Madras City Municipal Act, 1919 (Madras Act IV of 1919);`
  line
  line `^5[(oa) "National Capital Region" means the National Capital Region as defined in clause (f) of`
  line `section 2 of the National Capital Region Planning Board Act, 1985 (2 of 1985);]`
  line
  line `(p) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(q) "rolling stock" includes locomotives, engines, carriages (whether powered or not), wagons,`
  line `trollies and vehicles of all kinds moving or intended to move on rails;`
  line
  line `(r) "to erect", in relation to any building, includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any material alteration or enlargement of such building,`
  line
  line `(ii) conversion, by structural alteration, into a place for human habitation of such building not`
  line `originally constructed for human habitation,`
  line
  line `(iii) conversion into more than one place for human habitation of such building originally`
  line `constructed as one such place,`
  line
  line `(iv) conversion of two or more places of human habitation in such building into a greater`
  line `number of such places,`
  line
  line `(v) such alteration of such building as would alter the drainage or sanitary arrangements`
  line `therein or would materially affect its security, and`
  line
  line `(vi) the addition of any rooms in such building.`
  line
  line `(2) All other words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Indian Railways`
  line `Act, 1890 (9 of 1890), shall have the meanings, respectively, assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 2, for "arbitrator" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (e) (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs by Act 34 of 2009, s. 3, for "metropolitan city" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 4 (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24126)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `General Manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24126&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, for the purposes of this Act, appoint a General`
  line `Manager for every metro railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24127)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 3, for "metropolitan city" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24127&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may constitute an Advisory`
  line `Board, for every metro railway for the purpose of assisting or advising that Government on--`
  line
  line `(a) the formulation and co-ordination of plans for the development of metro railway and its`
  line expansion;
  line
  line `(b) the financing and execution of any project for the construction of the metro railway;`
  line
  line `(c) such other matters as may be referred to it for carrying out the purposes of this Act and in`
  line `particular for the purpose of ensuring that the functions of the metro railway administration are`
  line `exercised with due regard to the circumstances or conditions prevailing in, and requirements of, the`
  line `^1[metropolitan city, metropolitan area and the National Capital Region].`
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Board shall consist of such number of members (being officers of the Government)`
  line `not exceeding nine as may be appointed to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall appoint one of the members of the Advisory Board as its`
  line Chairman.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall publish in the Official Gazette the names of all the members of the`
  line `Advisory Board and the Chairman thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) The Advisory Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such procedure in`
  line `regard to the transaction of its business as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The members of the Advisory Board shall hold office for such term as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24128)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Committees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24128&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Advisory Board may constitute as many committees as it deems necessary`
  line `consisting wholly of members of such Board or wholly of other persons or partly of members of the`
  line `Board and partly of other persons for such purposes as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Every committee constituted under sub-section (1) shall meet at such times and places and shall`
  line `observe such procedure in regard to the transaction of its business as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be paid to the members of the committee who are not members of the Advisory Board,`
  line `such fees and allowances for attendance at the meetings of the committee and such travelling allowances`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24129)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to acquire land, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24129&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Where it appears to a metro railway administration that for the`
  line `construction of any metro railway or any other work connected therewith--`
  line
  line `(a) any land, building, street, road or passage, or`
  line
  line `(b) any right of user, or any right in the nature of easement, therein,`
  line
  line `is required for such construction or work, it shall apply to the Central Government in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed for acquiring such land, building, street, road or passage or such right of user or easement.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24130)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Publication of notification for acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24130&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application under section 6, the`
  line `Central Government, after being satisfied that the requirement mentioned therein is for a public purpose`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare its intention to acquire the land, building, street, road`
  line `or passage, or the right of user, or the right in the nature of easement, therein referred to in the`
  line application.
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1) shall give a brief description of the land, building, street,`
  line `road or passage.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall cause the substance of the notification to be published in such`
  line `places and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24131)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to enter for survey, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24131&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `On the issue of a notification under sub-section (1) of section 7,`
  line `it shall be lawful for the metro railway administration or any officer or other employee of the metro`
  line railway--
  line
  line `(a) to enter upon and survey and take level of the land, building, street, road or passage specified`
  line `in the notification;`
  line
  line `(b) to dig or bore into the sub-soil;`
  line
  line `(c) to set out the intended work;`
  line
  line `(d) to mark such levels, boundaries or lines by placing marks and cutting trenches;`
  line
  line `(e) to do all other acts necessary to ascertain whether the metro railway can be laid upon or under`
  line `the land, building, street, road or passage, as the ease may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that while exercising any power under this section the metro railway administration or such`
  line `officer or other employee shall cause as little damage or injury as possible to such land, building, street,`
  line `road or passage, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24132)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Hearing of objection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24132&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person interested in the land, building, street, road or passage`
  line `may, within twenty-one days from the ^1[date of publication under sub-section (3) of section 7 of the`
  line `substance of the notification under sub-section (1) of that section] object to the construction of the metro`
  line `railway or any other work connected therewith upon or under the land, building, street, road or passage,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, where the substance of the notification under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7 is published on different dates at different places, the last of such dates shall`
  line `be deemed to be the date on which substance of the notification has been published.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every objection under sub-section (1) shall be made to the competent authority in writing and`
  line `shall set out the grounds thereof and the competent authority shall give the objector an opportunity of`
  line `being heard, either in person or ^2[by an agent or] by a legal practitioner, and may, after hearing all such`
  line `objections and after making such further enquiry, if any, as the competent authority thinks necessary, by`
  line `order, either allow or disallow the objections.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section "legal practitioner" has the same meaning as in`
  line `clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961).`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made by the competent authority under sub-section (2) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 4, for certain words, brackets and figures (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24133)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Declaration of acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Proviso added by Act 42 of 1987, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-12-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24133&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where no objection under sub-section (1) of section 9 has been`
  line `made to the competent authority within the period specified therein or where the competent authority has`
  line `disallowed the objection under sub-section (2) of that section, the competent authority shall, as soon as`
  line `may be, submit a report accordingly to the Central Government and on receipt of such report, the Central`
  line `Government shall declare, by notification in the Official Gazette, that the land, building, street, road or`
  line `passage, or the right of user, or the right in the nature of easement, therein for laying the metro railway`
  line `should be acquired.`
  line
  line `(2) On the publication of the declaration under sub-section (1), the land, building, street, road or`
  line `passage, or the right of user, or the right in the nature of easement, therein shall vest absolutely in the`
  line `Central Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `(3) Where in respect of any land, building, street, road or passage, a notification has been published`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 7 either for its acquisition or for the acquisition of the right of user, or any`
  line `right in the nature of easement, therein, but no declaration under this section has been published within a`
  line `period of one year from the date of publication of that notification, the said notification shall cease to`
  line `have any effect:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that in computing the said period of one year, the period or periods during which any`
  line `action or proceeding to be taken in pursuance of the notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 7`
  line `[including any such action or proceeding pending immediately before the commencement of the Metro`
  line `Railways (Construction of Works) Amendment Act, 1987 (42 of 1987)] is stayed by an order of a Court,`
  line `whether granted before or after such commencement, shall be excluded.]`
  line
  line `(4) A declaration made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall not be called in`
  line `question in any court or by any other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24134)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to take possession of acquired land, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 5, for certain words, brackets and figures (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24134&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[Where any land, building, street, road or`
  line `passage has vested under sub-section (2) of section 10 and the amount determined by the competent`
  line `authority under section 13 with respect to such land, building, street, road or passage has been deposited,`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 14, with the competent authority by the Central Government], the`
  line `competent authority may by notice in writing direct the owner as well as any other person who may be in`
  line `possession of such land, building, street, road or passage to surrender or deliver possession thereof to the`
  line `competent authority or any person duly authorised by it in this behalf within sixty days of the service of`
  line `the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person refuses or fails to comply with any direction made under sub-section (1), the`
  line `competent authority shall apply,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any land, building, street, road or passage situated in any area falling within the`
  line `Presidency-town of Bombay, Calcutta or Madras, to the Commissioner of Police;`
  line
  line `(b) in the ease of any land, building, street, road or passage situated in any area other than the area`
  line `referred to in clause (a), to the Executive Magistrate,`
  line
  line `and such Commissioner or Magistrate, as the case may be, shall enforce the surrender of the land,`
  line `building, street, road or passage to the competent authority or to the person duly authorised by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24135)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Right to enter into the land where right of user, etc., is vested in the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24135&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where the right of user in, or any right in the nature of easement on, any land, building,`
  line `street, road or passage has vested in the Central Government under section 10, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `metro railway administration or any officer or other employee of the Central Government to enter and do`
  line `any other act necessary upon the land, building, street, road or passage for carrying out the construction of`
  line `the metro railway or any other work connected therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24136)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Determination of amount payable for acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24136&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any land, building, street, road`
  line `or passage is acquired under this Act, there shall be paid an amount which shall be determined ^1[by an`
  line `order of the competent authority].`
  line
  line `(2) Where the right of user in, or any right in the nature of an easement on, any land, building, street,`
  line `road or passage is acquired under this Act, there shall be paid an amount to the owner and any other`
  line `person whose right of enjoyment in that land, building, street, road or passage has been affected in any`
  line `manner whatsoever by reason of such acquisition an amount calculated at ten per cent. of the amount`
  line `determined under sub-section (1) for that land, building, street, road or passage.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Before proceeding to determine the amount under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the`
  line `competent authority shall give a public notice published in the prescribed manner inviting claims from all`
  line `persons interested in the land, building, street, road or passage, or the right of user or the right in the`
  line `nature of easement therein to be acquired.`
  line
  line `(2B) Such notice shall state the particulars of the land, building, street, road or passage acquired, or`
  line `the right of user or the right in the nature of easement therein acquired and shall require all persons`
  line `interested in such land, building, street, road or passage or right of user or right in the nature of easement`
  line `therein, to appear in person, or by an agent or by a legal practitioner referred to in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 9, before the competent authority, at a time and place therein mentioned (such time not being`
  line `earlier than fifteen days after the date of the publication of the notice) and to state the nature of their`
  line `respective interests in such land, building, street, road or passage or right of user or right in the nature of`
  line `easement therein.]`
  line
  line `(3) If the amount determined by the competent authority under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) is`
  line `not acceptable to either of the parties the amount shall, ^3[on an appeal preferred by either of the parties to`
  line `the appellate authority, within a period of sixty days from the date of the order appealed against, be`
  line `determined by an order of the appellate authority].`
  line
  line `(4) The competent authority or the ^4[appellate authority] while determining the amount under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (3), as the case may be, shall take into consideration--`
  line
  line `(a) the market value of the land, building, street, road or passage on the date of publication of the`
  line `notification under section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the damage, if any, sustained by the person interested at the time of taking possession of the`
  line `land, by reason of the severing of such land from other land;`
  line
  line `(c) the damage, if any, sustained by the person interested at the time of taking possession of the`
  line `land, building, street, road or passage by reason of the acquisition injuriously affecting his other`
  line `immovable property in any other manner, or his earnings;`
  line
  line `(d) if, in consequence of the acquisition of the land, building, street, road or passage, the person`
  line `interested is compelled to change his residence or place of business, the reasonable expenses, if any,`
  line `incidental to such change.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "by the competent authority" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 6, for "on an application by either of the parties, to the arbitrator, be determines by the`
  line `arbitrator" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "arbitrator" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24137)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Deposit and payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24137&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount determined ^1*** under section 13 shall be`
  line `deposited by the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed with the competent authority`
  line `^2[within such time as may be fixed by that authority].`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the amount has been deposited under sub-section (1), the competent`
  line `authority shall on behalf of the Central Government pay the amount to the person or persons entitled`
  line `thereto:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that where an appeal has been or is likely to be preferred under section 13 against the`
  line `order by which such amount was determined and the competent authority is satisfied for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing that it is necessary or expedient so to do, he may by order in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) require the person claiming payment of such amount to furnish as a condition of receiving`
  line `such payment such security as may be specified in the order; or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person fails to furnish such security, withhold the payment of the whole or any part of`
  line `such amount for such period as may be specified in the order.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where several persons claim to be interested in the amount deposited under sub-section (1), the`
  line `competent authority shall determine the persons who in its opinion are entitled to receive the amount`
  line `payable to each of them.`
  line
  line `(4) If any dispute arises as to the apportionment of the amount or any part thereof or to any person to`
  line `whom the same or any part thereof is payable, the competent authority shall refer the dispute to the`
  line `decision of the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the limits of whose jurisdiction the land,`
  line `building, street, road or passage is situated.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the amount determined under section 13 by the ^4[appellate authority] is in excess`
  line `of the amount determined by the competent authority, the ^4[appellate authority] may award interest at`
  line `six per cent. per annum on such excess amount from the date of taking possession under section 11 till the`
  line `date of the actual deposit thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the amount determined by the ^4[appellate authority] is in excess of the amount determined`
  line `by the competent authority, the excess amount together with interest, if any, awarded under`
  line `sub-section (5) shall be deposited by the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed with`
  line `the competent authority and the provisions of sub-sections (2) to (4) shall apply to such deposit.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "by the competent authority" omitted by s. 7, ibid, (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "before taking possession of the land, building, street, road or passage" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Proviso added by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 2, for "arbitrator" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24138)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Competent authority to have certain powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24138&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority shall`
  line `have, for the purposes of this Act, all the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commission for examination of witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (24139)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to inspect property under acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24139&sectionno=15A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Power to inspect property under acquisition.--The competent authority may, with or`
  line `without assistants or workmen, enter into or upon any land, building, street, road or passage, for the`
  line `purpose of performing his functions under this Act and make such enquiry, inspection, measurement and`
  line `take such photographs and prepare such memorandum thereof as he may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) no such entry shall be made except between the hours of sunrise and sunset and without giving`
  line `reasonable notice to--`
  line
  line `(a) the owner of, or the person interested in, the land, building, street, road or passage; or`
  line
  line `(b) the person whose right of user in or right in the nature of easement on the land, building,`
  line `street, road or passage is acquired; or`
  line
  line `(c) the person who sustains any loss or damage to the land, building, street, road or passage in`
  line `consequence of any direction given by the Central Government or any power exercised by the`
  line `metro railway administration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) sufficient opportunity shall in every instance be given to enable women, if any, to withdraw`
  line `from such land, building, street, road or passage;`
  line
  line `(iii) due regard shall always be had, so far as may be compatible with the exigencies of the`
  line `purpose for which the entry is made, to the social and religious usage of the person to whom notice as`
  line `aforesaid is given;`
  line
  line `(iv) the competent authority making the entry shall cause as little damage or injury as possible, to`
  line `the land, building, street, road or passage.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24140)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Competent authority and appellate authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for section 16 (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24140&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Competent authority and appellate authority.--(1) For every metro railway, the Central`
  line `Government shall, for the purposes of this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint--`
  line
  line `(i) a competent authority; and`
  line
  line `(ii) an appellate authority,`
  line
  line `for such area as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a competent authority unless he is holding, or`
  line `has held, a judicial office, not lower in rank than that of a subordinate judge.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as an appellate authority unless he is holding, or`
  line `has held, a judicial office, not lower in rank than that of a district judge.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "district judge" includes an additional district judge;`
  line
  line `(b) "subordinate judge" means subordinate judge in the judicial service of West Bengal, and`
  line `includes any judicial officer (by whatever name called) of an equivalent rank in the judicial service of`
  line `any other State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (24141)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers of the appellate authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24141&sectionno=16A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Powers of the appellate authority.--(1) The appellate authority may admit an appeal filed`
  line `after the expiry of the period referred to in section 13 or section 22 or section 25, as the case may be, if he`
  line `is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(2) For the disposal of an appeal under this Act, the appellate authority shall have the same powers`
  line `(including the powers under sections 15 and 15A), and shall, subject to the provisions of this section,`
  line `perform as nearly as may be the same duties as are conferred or imposed by this Act on the competent`
  line `authority in respect of the matters under Chapter III and Chapter IV.`
  line
  line `(3) The appellate authority may, if he thinks it expedient so to do, call in his aid one or more assessors`
  line `and hear the appeal wholly or partly with the aid of such assessors.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of determining the amount under any appeal before him, the appellate authority`
  line `may, after making such further enquiry or after taking such additional evidence, as may be necessary,`
  line `pass such order as he thinks fit, determining the amount, by confirming, modifying or annulling the order`
  line `appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) An order of the appellate authority determining the amount under this Act shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b:
  sectionId (24142)
  sectionNo 16B
  orderNo 19
  title `Competent authority, etc., to have certain inherent powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24142&sectionno=16B&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[16B. Competent authority, etc., to have certain inherent powers.--The competent authority and`
  line `the appellate authority may exercise powers of the nature referred to in section 151 of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), to the same extent and for the same purposes as such powers are exercisable`
  line `by civil courts.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_c:
  sectionId (24143)
  sectionNo 16C
  orderNo 20
  title `Enforcement of the orders of the competent authority and appellate authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24143&sectionno=16C&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_16_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[16C. Enforcement of the orders of the competent authority and appellate authority.--(1) Any`
  line `order made by the competent authority or the appellate authority determining any amount payable under`
  line `this Act may be enforced in the same manner as if such order were a decree made by a civil court in a suit`
  line `pending therein, and it shall be lawful for such authority to send, in the case of his inability to execute,`
  line `such order, to the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of whose jurisdiction`
  line `the order was made.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any order under sub-section (1) is required to be enforced by the principal civil court of`
  line `original jurisdiction, a certified copy of the order shall be produced to the proper officer of the court`
  line `required to enforce the order.`
  line
  line `(3) The production of such certified copy shall be sufficient evidence of the order.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon the production of such certified copy, the principal civil court of original jurisdiction shall`
  line `take the requisite steps for enforcing the order, in the same manner as if it had been a decree made by`
  line itself.]
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24144)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Land Acquisition Act 1 of 1894 not to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24144&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the Land Acquisition Act, 1894,`
  line `shall apply to an acquisition under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24145)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Functions of metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24145&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the control of the Central Government,`
  line `the metro railway administration shall, for the purpose of constructing any metro railway or any other`
  line `work connected therewith,--`
  line
  line `(a) make or construct in, upon, across, under or over any lands, buildings, streets, roads, railways`
  line `or tramways or any rivers, canals, brooks, streams or other waters or any drains, water-pipes,`
  line `gas-pipes, electric lines or telegraph lines, such temporary or permanent inclined planes, arches,`
  line `tunnels, culverts, embankments, aqueducts, bridges, ways or passages, as the metro railway`
  line `administration thinks proper;`
  line
  line `(b) alter the course of any rivers, canals, brooks, streams or water-courses for the purpose of`
  line `constructing tunnels, passages or other works over or under them and divert or alter as well`
  line `temporarily as permanently, the course of any rivers, canals, brooks, streams or water-courses or any`
  line `drains, water-pipes, gas-pipes, electric lines or telegraph lines or raise or sink the level thereof in`
  line `order the more conveniently to carry them over or under, as the metro railway administration thinks`
  line proper;
  line
  line `(c) make drains or conduits into, through or under, any lands adjoining the metro railway for the`
  line `purpose of conveying water from or to the metro railway;`
  line
  line `(d) erect or construct search houses, warehouses, offices and other buildings and such yards,`
  line `stations, engines, machinery, apparatus and other works and conveniences, as the metro railway`
  line `administration thinks proper;`
  line
  line `(e) alter, repair or discontinue such buildings, works and conveniences as aforesaid or any of`
  line `them, and substitute others in their stead;`
  line
  line `(f) draw, make or conduct such maps, plans, surveys or tests, as the metro railway administration`
  line `thinks proper;`
  line
  line `(g) do all other acts necessary for making, maintaining, altering or repairing and using the metro`
  line railway.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24146)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Powers of metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24146&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The metro railway administration shall, for the`
  line `purpose of ^1[performing its functions under section 18] have power--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter into contracts and leases and to execute all instruments necessary therefor;`
  line
  line `(b) to make such number of rail tracks as the Central Government may think necessary upon,`
  line `under, along or across any land, canal, river, street or road on or in the metro alignment and all other`
  line `works and conveniences in connection therewith;`
  line
  line `(c) ^2[to open, divert or temporarily close], as the case may be, any street, road, cable, trench, drain`
  line `(including a sewer), channel, ditch, culvert or any other device (whether for carrying of sullage,`
  line `sewage, offensive matter, polluted water, trade effluent, rain water, sub-soil water or any other`
  line `object), electric or gas supply line or tele-communication line, or telegraph installation, over, across`
  line `or under any land, building, street, road, railway or tramway;`
  line
  line `(d) to burrow tunnels;`
  line
  line `(e) to lay down signalling and other communication facilities, electric sub-stations, supply lines`
  line `and other works;`
  line
  line `(f) to regulate drilling of tubewells or sinking of wells, public or private, in the proximate vicinity`
  line `of the metro alignment;`
  line
  line `(g) to do all other things necessary or expedient for the exercise of any of the aforesaid powers.`
  line
  line `(2) While exercising any powers under sub-section (1), the metro railway administration shall take`
  line `such precautionary measures as are necessary, shall do as little damage as possible and shall be liable`
  line `only for the damage or cost actually suffered or incurred by any person as a result of the exercise of such`
  line powers.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "to open or divert" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24147)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Development over metro alignment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24147&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who proposes to develop any land or`
  line `building along or on the metro alignment shall, before commencing such development and without in any`
  line `way limiting his obligation under any other Act to obtain any approval or consent, submit to the metro`
  line `railway administration details of the proposed development and shall comply with any conditions`
  line `imposed by the metro railway administration in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The metro railway administration shall, while imposing any condition under sub-section (1), have`
  line `regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the safety of the metro railway;`
  line
  line `(b) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24148)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to prohibit or regulate construction of buildings and excavation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 12, for "ten metres" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24148&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do for facilitating the construction of any`
  line `metro railway or for ensuring the safety of any metro railway, it may, by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette,--
  line
  line `(a) direct that no building or any such development as may be specified in the notification shall`
  line `be constructed or made above the metro alignment or on any land within such distance, not exceeding`
  line `^1[twenty metres] on either side of the metro alignment, as may be specified in the notification and`
  line `where there is any building on such land also direct the owner of, or the person having control over,`
  line `such building to demolish such building or to make such additions or alterations to such building as`
  line `may be specified in the notification or to desist from making any such development and within such`
  line `period as may be specified in the notification;`
  line
  line `(b) direct temporary evacuation of all persons together with any movable property or animal that`
  line `may be in the custody, control or possession of such persons from any building situated above the`
  line `metro alignment or in any area within a distance not exceeding twenty metres on either side of such`
  line `alignment and within such period as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any notification under this clause, the Central Government shall provide`
  line `every such person temporarily with alternative accommodation, which in its opinion is suitable, free of`
  line `cost, or an amount, which in its opinion is sufficient, to procure a temporary alternative accommodation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any property is needed or likely to be needed for providing any alternative accommodation`
  line `under the proviso to clause (b) of sub-section (1), such property shall be deemed to be needed for`
  line `a public purpose under section 3 of the Requisitioning and Acquisition of Immovable Property Act,`
  line `1952 (30 of 1952), and the competent authority under that Act shall requisition the property in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of that Act and such provisions shall, in relation to such requisition, apply`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(3) In specifying the distance under clause (a) of sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have`
  line `regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature and the requirement of the metro railway;`
  line
  line `(b) the safety of the building;`
  line
  line `(c) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any notification has been issued under sub-section (1) directing the owner or the person`
  line `having control over any building to demolish such building or to make additions or alterations to such`
  line `building or to desist from making any development specified in such notification, a copy of the`
  line `notification containing such direction shall be served on the owner of, or the person having control over,`
  line `such building, as the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(i) by delivering or tendering it to such owner or person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if it cannot be delivered or tendered, by delivering or tendering it to the agent of such owner`
  line `or person or any adult male member of the family of such owner or person or by affixing a copy`
  line `thereof on the outer door or on some conspicuous part of the premises in which such owner or person`
  line `is known to have last resided or carried on business or personally worked for gain; or failing service`
  line `by these means;`
  line
  line `(iii) by post.`
  line
  line `(5) Every person shall be bound to comply with any direction contained in any notification issued`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24149)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Payment of amount for prohibition of construction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24149&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in consequence of any`
  line `direction contained in any notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 21 any person sustains any`
  line `loss or damage, such person shall be paid an amount which shall be determined ^1[by an order of the`
  line `competent authority] in the first instance.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount determined by the competent authority is not acceptable to either of the parties, the`
  line `amount shall,`
  line `^2[on an appeal preferred by either of the parties, within sixty days from the date of the order`
  line `of the competent authority, to the appellate authority, be determined by an order of the appellate`
  line authority].
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority or the ^3[appellate authority], while determining the amount under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be, shall take into consideration--`
  line
  line `(i) the loss or damage sustained by such person in his earnings;`
  line
  line `(ii) the diminution, if any, of the market value of the land or building immediately after the date`
  line `of publication of such notification;`
  line
  line `(iii) where in pursuance of any direction any building has been demolished or any additions or`
  line `alterations to such building have been made or any development has been desisted by such person,`
  line `the damage sustained by him in consequence of such demolition or the making of such additions or`
  line `alterations or the desisting from making such development and the expenses incurred by such person`
  line `for such demolition or additions or alterations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the expenses incurred for such demolition or additions or alterations shall not be taken`
  line `into consideration if such demolition or additions or alterations has or have been done by the metro`
  line `railway administration under sub-section (2) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(iv) if any such person is compelled to change his residence or place of business the reasonable`
  line `expenses, if any, that may have to be incurred by him incidental to such change.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 13, for "by the competent authority" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by s. 13, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 2, for "arbitrator" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24150)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to underpin building or otherwise strengthen it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24150&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the metro railway`
  line `administration is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do for facilitating the construction of`
  line `any metro railway or for ensuring the safety of any metro railway, it may, underpin or otherwise`
  line `strengthen any building within such radius not exceeding fifty metres from the metro alignment.`
  line
  line `(2) The metro railway administration shall give to the owner or occupier of such building at least ten`
  line `days notice in writing before undertaking the work of underpinning or otherwise strengthening the`
  line `building:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the metro railway administration is satisfied that an emergency exists, no such`
  line `notice shall be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the underpinning or strengthening was executed in connection with--`
  line
  line `(a) the carrying out of the works upon the land where any building is situated, or`
  line
  line `(b) the construction or operation of any metro railway,`
  line
  line `the metro railway administration may, at any time after the underpinning or strengthening of such`
  line `building is completed and before the expiration of a period of twelve months,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case referred to in clause (a), from the completion of such works; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case referred to in clause (b), from the date on which traffic was opened in the metro`
  line railway,
  line
  line `enter upon and survey such building and do such further underpinning or strengthening thereon as it may`
  line `deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24151)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to enter, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24151&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to making survey, or to ascertaining the nature or`
  line `condition, of any land or building for the purpose of construction of any metro railway or any other work`
  line `connected therewith, the metro railway administration or any person authorised by that administration`
  line `may, at any reasonable hour in the day time and after giving reasonable notice to the owner or occupier of`
  line `such land or building, enter upon or into such land or building in, along, over or near the metro alignment`
  line to--
  line
  line `(a) inspect the same;`
  line
  line `(b) make measurements and drawings and take photographs thereof and such other suitable`
  line `measures as may be necessary to explore and check up, by digging trial pits or otherwise, the`
  line `foundation of any building in the vicinity of the metro alignment;`
  line
  line `(c) take such other measures as the said administration deems necessary and proper.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the powers conferred on it under section 19, the metro railway administration`
  line `may, by writing, request any person or body of persons controlling any sewer, storm water drain, pipe,`
  line `wire or cable to carry out at the expense of the metro railway administration any alterations thereto which`
  line `that administration is authorised or may be required to carry out to meet any particular situation for`
  line `carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) If any difference or dispute arises between the metro railway administration and the person or`
  line `body of persons referred to in sub-section (2) in relation to any such alterations or the cost thereof, such`
  line `difference or dispute shall be determined by the Central Government in consultation (wherever necessary)`
  line `with the State Government and the decision of the Central Government in this regard shall not be called`
  line `in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24152)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 29
  title `Amount payable for damage, loss or injury.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24152&sectionno=25&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the metro railway administration`
  line `exercises any power conferred on it by or under this Act and in consequence thereof any damage, loss or`
  line `injury is sustained by any person interested in any land, building, street, road or passage, the metro`
  line `railway administration shall be liable to pay to such person for such damage, loss or injury such amount`
  line `as may be determined by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount determined by the competent authority under sub-section (1) is not acceptable to`
  line `either of the parties, the amount payable shall, ^1[on an appeal preferred by either of the parties, within`
  line `sixty days from the date of the order of the competent authority, to the appellate authority, be determined`
  line `by an order of the appellate authority].`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority or the ^2[appellate authority] while determining the amount under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be, shall have due regard to the damage, loss or injury`
  line `sustained by any person interested in the land, building, street, road or passage by reason of--`
  line
  line `(i) the removal of trees or standing crops, if any;`
  line
  line `(ii) the temporary severance of the land, building, street, road or passage;`
  line
  line `(iii) any injury to any other property whether movable or immovable.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) The procedure and the manner of deposit and payment of the amount payable for acquiring any`
  line `land, building, street, road or passage or any right of user in or any right in the nature of easement on any`
  line `land, building, street, road or passage shall be followed in the case of the procedure and the manner of`
  line `deposit and payment of the amount determined by the competent authority or the appellate authority`
  line `under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 14, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "arbitrator" (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (24153)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 30
  title `Right to claim for damages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24153&sectionno=26&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No claim in respect of any damage, loss or injury alleged to have`
  line `been caused as a consequence of construction of any metro railway or any other work connected`
  line `therewith under this Act shall lie against the metro railway administration unless such claim is made`
  line `within a period of twelve months from the date of completion of the construction of such metro railway or`
  line `other work in the area in which such damage, loss or injury is caused.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (24154)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 31
  title `Appointment and duties of commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24154&sectionno=27&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint as many`
  line `persons as it thinks fit by name or by virtue of their office to be commissioners of metro railway.`
  line
  line `(2) Every commissioner shall--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect the metro railway with a view to determining whether it is fit to be opened for public`
  line `carriage of passengers and report thereon to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) make such periodical or other inspections of any metro railway or of any rolling stock used`
  line `thereon as the Central Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) perform such other duties as may be imposed on him by or under this Act or any other`
  line `enactment for the time being in force relating to railways or required by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (24155)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 32
  title `Powers of commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24155&sectionno=28&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the control of the Central Government every`
  line `commissioner shall have the power--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter upon and inspect any metro railway or any rolling stock used thereon;`
  line
  line `(b) to make any enquiry or to take any measurement as he thinks fit for the performance of his`
  line `duties under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) by an order in writing under his hand and official seal addressed to any metro railway`
  line `administration, to require the attendance before him of any officer or other employee of the metro`
  line `railway and to require answers or returns, to such enquiries as he thinks fit to make, from such officer`
  line `or other employee or from the said administration;`
  line
  line `(d) to require the production of any book or other documents belonging to, or in the possession or`
  line `control of, any metro railway administration which it appears to him to be necessary to inspect for the`
  line `performance of his duties by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (24156)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 33
  title `Facilities to be afforded to commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24156&sectionno=29&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every metro railway administration shall afford to`
  line `every commissioner all reasonable facilities for performing the duties or exercising the powers imposed`
  line `or conferred upon him by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (24157)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 34
  title `Surplus land to be sold or otherwise disposed of.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24157&sectionno=30&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Every metro railway administration may,`
  line `with the previous approval of the Central Government, sell or otherwise dispose of any land vested in the`
  line `Central Government under the provisions of this Act when such land is no longer required for the`
  line `purposes of the metro railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (24158)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 35
  title `Notice of accidents and enquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24158&sectionno=31&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any accident occurs during the construction of any`
  line `metro railway or at any stage subsequent thereto as a consequence of such construction and the accident`
  line `results in, or is likely to have resulted in, loss of human being or animal or damage to any property, it`
  line `shall be the duty of the metro railway administration to give notice to the Central Government of the`
  line `occurrence of any such loss or damage in such form and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a notice under sub-section (1), the Central Government may, if it thinks fit, appoint`
  line `a commission to enquire into the accident and report as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the cause of such accident;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which and the extent to which the provisions of this Act or any other Act for the`
  line `time being in force in so far as those provisions regulate and govern the safety of any person, animal`
  line `or property, have been complied with.`
  line
  line `(3) The commission appointed under sub-section (2), while holding an enquiry, shall have all the`
  line `powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery or production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commission for examination of witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (24159)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to alter the entries in the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 3, for "metropolitan city" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24159&sectionno=32&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) add to the Schedule the metro alignment in respect of a ^1`
  line `[metropolitan city, metropolitan area`
  line `and the National Capital Region] to which this Act is made applicable under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 1;`
  line
  line `(b) alter any metro alignment specified in the Schedule if it is of opinion that such alteration is`
  line `necessary for the construction and maintenance of the metro railway to which such alignment relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it is issued, be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (24160)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 37
  title `Prohibition of obstruction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24160&sectionno=33&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without any reasonable cause or excuse, obstruct`
  line `any person with whom the metro railway administration has entered into a contract, in the performance or`
  line `execution by such person of such contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (24161)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 38
  title `Local authorities to assist.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24161&sectionno=34&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Every local authority shall render such help and assistance and`
  line `furnish such information to the metro railway administration as that administration may require for`
  line `discharging its functions and shall make available to the said administration for inspection and`
  line `examination such records, maps, plans and other documents as may be necessary for the discharge of`
  line `such functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (24162)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 39
  title `Prohibition of removal of marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24162&sectionno=35&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No person shall remove any marks placed or fill up any`
  line `trench cut for the purpose of marking levels, boundaries or lines by the metro railway administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (24163)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 40
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with directions issued under section 21.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 41 of 1982, s. 15 (w.e.f. 15-5-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24163&sectionno=36&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person`
  line `wilfully fails to comply with any direction contained in any notification issued under section 21, he shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), if any person fails to demolish any building`
  line `or make additions or alterations thereto in pursuance of any direction contained in any notification issued`
  line `under section 21 within the period specified in the notification, then, subject to such rules as the Central`
  line `Government may make in this behalf, it shall be competent for any officer authorised by the metro`
  line `railway administration in this behalf to demolish such building or make necessary additions or alterations`
  line thereto.
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2A) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), if any person fails to vacate temporarily`
  line `any building together with any movable property or animal that may be in his custody, control or`
  line `possession in pursuance of any direction contained in any notification issued under section 21 within the`
  line `period specified in the notification, the competent authority may enforce the direction of temporary`
  line `evacuation physically by taking such police help, as may be considered by him necessary, and for this`
  line `purpose the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11 shall, as far as may be, apply.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (24164)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 41
  title `General provision for punishment of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24164&sectionno=37&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision of this`
  line `Act or of any rule made thereunder shall, if no other penalty is provided for such contravention elsewhere`
  line `in this Act or the rules, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (24165)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 42
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24165&sectionno=38&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (24166)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 43
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24166&sectionno=39&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `No suit or application for injunction shall lie in any court against the`
  line `Central Government or the metro railway administration or any officer or other employee of that`
  line `Government or the metro railway or any person working for or on behalf of the metro railway`
  line `administration, in respect of any work done or purported to have been done or intended to be done by it or`
  line `the said administration or such officer or other employee or such person in connection with the`
  line `construction of any metro railway or any other work connected therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (24167)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 44
  title `Effect of Act and rules, etc., inconsistent with other enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24167&sectionno=40&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act`
  line `or any rule made or any notification issued thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything`
  line `inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act or in any instrument having effect`
  line `by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (24168)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 45
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24168&sectionno=41&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government, the metro railway administration or any officer or other`
  line `employee of that Government or the metro railway for anything which is in good faith done or intended to`
  line `be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or the`
  line `metro railway administration or any officer or other employee of that Government or the metro railway`
  line `for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (24169)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24169&sectionno=42&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions,`
  line `which appears to it to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall, in relation to any metropolitan city, be made after the expiry of a`
  line `period of two years from the date on which this Act applies or is made applicable to such metropolitan`
  line `city under sub-section (3) of section 1.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (24170)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 47
  title `Application of the Indian Railways Act, 1890.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24170&sectionno=43&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act,`
  line `the provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, the Indian Railways`
  line `Act, 1890 (9 of 1890).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (24171)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24171&sectionno=44&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the times and places at which the Advisory Board shall meet and the procedure in regard to`
  line `transaction of business by the Advisory Board under sub-section (5) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office of the members of the Advisory Board under sub-section (6) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the times and places at which the committees shall meet and the procedure in regard to`
  line `transaction of business by the committees under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) the payment of fees, allowances and travelling allowances to the members of the committee`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which an application for acquisition shall be made under section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the places at which and the manner in which the substance of the notification shall be`
  line `published under sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which the amount shall be deposited with the competent authority under`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (6) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(h) the matters to be specified under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(i) the matters to be specified under clause (c) of sub-section (3) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(j) the form in which and the time within which a notice shall be given under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 31;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (24172)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 49
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089&sectionId=24172&sectionno=45&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00005_197833_1517807325089
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act any proceeding, for the acquisition of`
  line `any land, under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), for the purpose of any metro railway,`
  line `pending immediately before the commencement of this Act before any court or other authority shall be`
  line `continued and be disposed of under that Act as if this Act had not come into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
